                "answer_1": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: Taboos are norms so strong that they often bring revulsion if violated. Therefore, one would likely suffer more than fines if violating a taboo. LO 2.2 Know the components of symbolic culture: gestures, language, values, norms, sanctions, folkways, mores, and taboos; also explain the Sapir-Whorf hypothesis."
                },
